    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2013-08-02</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2013-08-20T20:09:39Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Forty Hours is Full Time Act of 2013 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to the employer mandate to provide health care coverage, to: (1) modify the formula for calculating the number of full-time employees employed by an applicable large employer subject to the mandate; and (2) define a &quot;full-time employee&quot; as an employee who is employed on average at least 40 hours per week (currently, 30 hours).</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
